Few things to unravel here:

> Leaderboard vs rewards table
- The ranking on leaderboard is based on hashrate in 24 hours (you can peek at the share-value column if you want). It’s a running average. 
- The rewards are calculated based on the share value a miner submits every UTC day (starts and ends at midnight).
- This is a super fair approach to reward for actual work done instead of raw hash power. This rewards good miners who provide good block hashes. 

> Previous design vs New design
- Previous design disbursed you the share-value u mined through Alpha tokens only. 
- New design gives you the amount in btc instead (with a 2% fee) and upto 3% of the total share-value u mined as Alpha value as a bonus. 
- The fee that is deducted is given back to Alpha holders - so it incentivizes you to hold & accumulate alpha
- The new pool design actually competes with the most popular pools out there who disburse btc. 
The added Alpha is a bonus for you for being part of the Bittensor ecosystem and contributing to the subnet (soon with governance as well)

> Rewards disbursement
- Currently we are disbursing rewards through btc addresses. As you know, this is a little longer process. For now, Latent is covering all the fee associated with the transfer. 
- Very soon (might be today) we will be putting out support for lightening addresses which will make the transfer super fast and efficient with no fee. 

> Schedule
